SIMPLE: eruptive
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eruptive
<hw>E*rup"tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧ruptif</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Breaking out or
bursting forth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The sudden glance⟦br⟧
Appears far south <qex>eruptive</qex> through the cloud.</q>
<rj><qau>Thomson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Attended with eruption or
efflorescence, or producing it; <as>as, an <ex>eruptive</ex>
fever</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Produced by eruption; <as>as,
<ex>eruptive</ex> rocks, such as the igneous or volcanic</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eruptive</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Eruptive
<hw>E*rup"tive</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>An eruptive
rock.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Erwinia</ent>⟦br⟧
